# Documentation Rules

## When to Update Docs

| Change | Update |
|--------|--------|
| New feature | docs/product/, docs/architecture/ |
| Schema change | docs/architecture/DATABASE.md |
| Security fix | docs/security/SECURITY_AUDIT.md |
| New env var | .env.example, AGENTS.md, README.md |
| Resolved tech debt | docs/roadmaps/TECH_DEBT_ROADMAP.md |

## Standards

- Date-stamp audit documents
- Include severity and priority for findings
- Link related docs at bottom of each file
- Keep AGENTS.md under 200 lines, imperative tone
- Do not duplicate audit content in README — link instead

## AI Agent Files

Keep synchronized: AGENTS.md, PROJECT_MEMORY.md, CLAUDE.md

Reference: `docs/standards/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md`
